            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.161.b",
            "tibetan": "བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་ཀྱིས་དེ་ཁྱོད་ལ་ཇི་ལྟར་ལུང་བསྟན་པ་དེ་བཞིན་དུ་ཟུང་ལ་བརྩོན་པར་གྱིས་ཤིག་ཅེས་སྨྲས་ནས།",
            "english": "Retain the Bhagavān’s instruction exactly as it is given to you, and apply yourself to it!’ He then disappeared suddenly.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-42",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/322"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.161.b",
            "tibetan": "ལྷ་དེ་དེ་ཉིད་དུ་མི་སྣང་བར་གྱུར་ཏོ། །བཙུན་པ་བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་དེའི་སླད་དུ་བདག་འདིའི་དོན་ཡོངས་སུ་ཞུའོ།",
            "english": "Therefore, Venerable Bhagavān, I have come to ask you the meaning of this.”",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-42",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/322"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "།བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་ཀྱིས་བཀའ་སྩལ་པ། དགེ་སློང་ཁྱོད་ཀྱིས་ལྷ་དེ་ཤེས་སམ།",
            "english": "The Bhagavān asked, “Monk, do you know that deity?”",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-45",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "དགེ་སློང་དེས་གསོལ་པ། བཙུན་པ་བདག་གིས་ལྷ་དེ་མ་འཚལ་ཏོ། །བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་ཀྱིས་བཀའ་སྩལ་པ།",
            "english": "“Sir, I do not know that deity,” the monk replied.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-45",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "ལྷའི་བུ་དེ་ནི་སུམ་ཅུ་རྩ་གསུམ་གྱི་ལྷ་རྣམས་ཀྱི་སྡེ་དཔོན་ཏེ།",
            "english": "“This deity is a general of the gods of the Heaven of the Thirty-Three.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-47",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "ཙན་དན་ཞེས་བྱའོ། །དགེ་སློང་དེས་གསོལ་པ།",
            "english": "His name is Candana.”",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-47",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "བཙུན་པ་བདག་མཚན་མོ་བཟང་པོའི་མདོ་སྡེ་ཐོས་པར་འཚལ་ལོ། །བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་ཀྱིས་བཀའ་སྩལ་པ།",
            "english": "“Sir, I wish to hear the teaching of Auspicious Night ,” the monk entreated.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-47",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "དགེ་སློང་ཁྱོད་དེའི་ཕྱིར་ལེགས་པར་རབ་ཏུ་ཉོན་ལ་ཡིད་ལ་ཟུང་ཤིག་དང་། ངས་ཁྱོད་ལ་བཤད་པར་བྱའོ།",
            "english": "The Bhagavān replied, “Then, monk, listen well and carefully, and pay attention!",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-51",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "།དགེ་སློང་ཆོས་གསུམ་དང་ལྡན་ན་དགེ་སློང་མཚན་མོ་བཟང་པོའི་མདོ་སྡེ་ལ་གནས་པ་ཞེས་བྱའོ།",
            "english": "I will teach you. Monk, when monks are endowed with three special qualities, they are called those who abide by the teaching of Auspicious Night",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-51",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "།གསུམ་གང་ཞེ་ན།",
            "english": "Which three?",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-51",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "འདི་ལྟ་སྟེ།",
            "english": "They are as follows:",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-51",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "འདས་པ་ལ་རྗེས་སུ་ཕྲད་པར་མི་བྱེད་པ་དང་། མ་འོངས་པ་ལ་རེ་བ་མེད་པ་དང་། ད་ལྟར་བྱུང་བའི་ཆོས་རྣམས་ཀྱིས་མི་འཕྲོགས་པར་གནས་པའི་ཆོས་ཅན་ཏེ། ཆོས་གསུམ་པོ་དེ་དག་དང་ལྡན་ན་དགེ་སློང་མཚན་མོ་བཟང་པོའི་མདོ་སྡེ་ལ་གནས་པ་ཞེས་བྱའོ།",
            "english": "By possessing the three special qualities of (1) not following after the past, (2) not hoping for the future, and (3) remaining uncaptivated by presently arisen states, a monk is known as someone who follows the teaching of Auspicious Night",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-51",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "།བཅོམ་ལྡན་འདས་ཀྱིས་དེ་སྐད་ཅེས་བཀའ་སྩལ་ཏེ།",
            "english": "This is what the Bhagavān said.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-54",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.a",
            "tibetan": "བདེ་བར་གཤེགས་པས་དེ་སྐད་གསུངས་ནས། སྟོན་པས་གཞན་ཡང་འདི་སྐད་གསུང་ངོ་།",
            "english": "After the Sugata had thus spoken, he furthermore stated the following:",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-54",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/323"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།འདས་ལ་རྗེས་སུ་ཕྲད་མི་བྱེད།",
            "english": "“Do not follow after the past",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།མ་འོངས་པ་ལ་རེ་བ་མེད།",
            "english": "Or hope for the future!",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།འདས་པ་གང་ཡིན་དེ་འགགས་ཏེ།",
            "english": "What is past has ceased to exist;",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།མ་འོངས་དེ་ནི་མ་ཕྱིན་པའོ།",
            "english": "The future has not yet arrived. {1} “Having thoroughly examined",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།གང་དག་ད་ལྟར་བྱུང་བའི་ཆོས།",
            "english": "Each presently arisen thing,",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།དེ་དང་དེ་ལ་རབ་བལྟས་ནས།",
            "english": "And knowing each, one understands,",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།རྣམ་པར་རྟོག་པས་མི་འཕྲོགས་པར། །དེ་དག་ཐམས་ཅད་ཁོང་དུ་ཆུད།",
            "english": "Undeceived by false conceptions.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-55",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།སང་ཙམ་ཤི་ཡང་སུ་ཤེས་ཀྱིས།",
            "english": "‘Will I die tomorrow?’ Who knows?",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-59",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།དེ་རིང་ཉིད་དུ་བརྟུན་ཏེ་བྱ།",
            "english": "Today the effort should be made.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-59",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།འཆི་བདག་སྡེ་ཆེན་དེ་དང་ནི།",
            "english": "The lord of death and his great army",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-59",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།བདག་ཏུ་བཤེས་པ་མ་ཡིན་ནོ།",
            "english": "Do not come to offer friendship.",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-59",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།སེམས་ཅན་ཀུན་དང་སྲོག་ཆགས་ཀུན།",
            "english": "“May all sentient beings and creatures",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-63",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།འབྱུང་པོ་ཀུན་དང་ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱང་།",
            "english": "And the entirety of living things",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-63",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།བདེ་བ་འབའ་ཞིག་གྲུབ་གྱུར་ཏེ།",
            "english": "Achieve perfect happiness,",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-63",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།ཐམས་ཅད་ཉོན་མོངས་མེད་པར་ཤོག །ཐམས་ཅད་བཟང་པོ་མཐོང་གྱུར་ཏེ།",
            "english": "And be free from the afflictions! May all good things be seen,",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-63",
            "creation_tool": "tibetan-aligner/84000",
            "volume": "72",
            "folio_xmlId": "UT4CZ5369-I1KG9198-0000/side/324"
        },
        {
            "creation_method": "v3",
            "notes": [],
            "flags": "",
            "folio": "F.162.b",
            "tibetan": "།གང་ཡང་སྡིག་པར་མ་གྱུར་ཅིག །དེ་ལྟར་གནས་ཤིང་རབ་བརྩོན་ལ།",
            "english": "And may nothing evil at all occur! {4} “So that one maintains this and applies oneself",
            "passage-xmlId": "UT22084-072-013-63",
